    Load Boundaries to Molecule Experiment Object

    loadBoundaries.Rd

    This function takes a Molecule Experiment (ME) object as input and enriches it with boundary data from a variety of assays. The currently supported assays are:

    • Sub-sector polygons

    • Sub-concentric polygons

    • Super-sector polygons

    • Super-concentric polygons

    The function internally processes each assay, extracts respective boundary information, and updates the original ME object with this new data.

    loadBoundaries(me, ...)

    Arguments

    me

    A MoleculeExperiment (ME) object

    ...

    arguments passed to GenerateFeatureData

    Value

    An enriched Molecule Experiment (ME) object that includes boundary information for the supported assays.

    Examples

    data(example_me)
me <- loadBoundaries(me)
me
